dismissalText.commentary: Gary Wilson not out 70 (88b 4x4 0x6 127m) SR: 79.54
Ed Joyce c Chigumbura b Nyumbu 53 (88b 2x4 1x6 110m) SR: 60.22

dismissalComment.html: well, where's this come from? Joyce was looking to open up against Nyumbu, and he cleared his front leg aiming for a slash through the off side. But he hit the ball neither high in the air or along the ground, and picked out Elton Chigumbura to perfection at extra cover. The Zimbabwe captain holds the catch, and an 83 run partnership is broken

well, where's this come from? Joyce was looking to open up against Nyumbu, and he cleared his front leg aiming for a slash through the off side. But he hit the ball neither high in the air or along the ground, and picked out Elton Chigumbura to perfection at extra cover. The Zimbabwe captain holds the catch, and an 83 run partnership is broken

Waller holds a catch! He would have been under some pressure as this ball rocketed towards him. Kevin O'Brien had jumped down the crease at Nyumbu, who came round the wicket, but the bat turned in his hands as he aimed down the ground. He still got a decent enough connection, but not enough to get the ball past Waller, who set himself under the chance at long off and managed to hold on. That'll be a relief for him.

headshotImage.caption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: a maiden international wicket for Wellington Masakadza! And it took a good catch out in the deep to complete it. Mooney bent low down and then aimed a slog sweep at the Tobacco Stand on the Western side of the ground, but got rather more height than distance. Jongwe was the fielder out there, and he initially ran in before backpedalling a couple of steps and setting himself for the catch. He held on cleanly, and Wellington bent down on one knee midpitch in celebration

another for Wellington! Dockrell jumped down the track but swung past a delivery that gripped and turned past his outside edge. There was no mistake from Mutumbami with the gloves, and he's cleanly stumped. Ireland are fading somewhat now after their good start

dismissalText.commentary: Paul Stirling c Sikandar Raza b Panyangara 24 (24b 5x4 0x6 35m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: soft dismissal! Panyangara floated down a gentle delivery, full on middle and leg, and Stirling couldn't keep his shot down. He seemed to almost pull out of the shot as he played it, and the ball travelled very gently indeed to Raza at midwicket. He holds a simple chance, and Zimbabwe have a much-needed breakthrough

dismissalText.commentary: William Porterfield c Masakadza b Chibhabha 9 (31b 1x4 0x6 43m) SR: 29.03

dismissalComment.html: that is a fine catch! That's why Wellington Masakadza is at point then. Porterfield stepped back and aimed to cut Chibhabha away, but couldn't keep the shot down. The youngest Masakadza brother, who is left handed, tumbled to his right to hold onto the chance, which was firmly struck. Welcome to international cricket Wellington

Balbirnie leaned back to cut, and got a fierce connection on the ball, but couldn't keep the shot down. Masakadza tumbles to his right and holds the ball about a foot off the ground. He's enjoying his debut so far

dismissalComment.html: what's happened here? Ireland went up in unison as the ball passed Ervine's bat. Wilson also whipped the bails off, but it wasn't the square leg umpire who gave him out. Yep, that's caught behind, and it's a huge dismissal for Ireland.

stumped! He's got him, and the partnership is broken. Dockrell hasn't been turning the ball, and it's the lack of turn that has done him in. The ball was flighted outside off, and Williams stretched forward to drive. But the ball rushed straight on past him, and Wilson had the bails off in a flash. Ireland have an opening here.

edged, and gone! Well, he edged a couple in the last over, and now one has landed in Wilson's gloves. The ball looked an innocuous one, wide outside off stump, but Chigumbura cut underneath it and Wilson held a sharp chance. Zimbabwe's target is only 96 runs away, but Ireland are keeping themselves in the hunt.

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller c Thompson b Murtagh 1 (12b 0x4 0x6 15m) SR: 8.33

dismissalComment.html: he's gone! A scratchy innings comes to an end. There was only one fielder left out in the deep, and Waller has picked him out to perfection. Murtagh dug the ball in, and the batsman stepped back to pull in the air ... and Thompson didn't have to move at deep midwicket.

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Jongwe run out (Joyce/McBrine) 5 (9b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, what's happened here? Raza whipped an offspinner off his pads but it went very close to the square leg fielder. Jongwe called for the run, but Raza sent him back. Jongwe was already halfway down the pitch by that stage, and Joyce's throw caught him well short.

dismissalText.commentary: Wellington Masakadza run out (Joyce/Porterfield) 10 (18b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: drama! Is there another twist in this tale? Raza lofted a length delivery out to deep cover, where it fell safely. They took the first two runs easily, but Raza wanted a third. Masakadza committed to the run straight away, but it was never on. Joyce's throw from the deep went to Porterfield at cover, who relayed it to the keeper, catching the batsman well short.

commentPreTextItems.html: 2 off 7, last ball of the over. Yet another Zimbabwe v Ireland game goes down to the wire. Why don't these teams play each other more often?

commentTextItems.html: what a way to finish the match! Panyangara steps down the track to meet the ball on the half volley,and crunches the ball straight down the ground for four! Scenes!

commentPostTextItems.html: 5.35pm Though Raza's knock sealed the result, the character of this game was decided by the spinners on both sides. Zimbabwe's combination of John Nyumbu, Sean Williams and debutant Wellington Masakadza took a combined 5 for 125 in 29 overs, while George Dockrell was a handful in the afternoon and Ireland's slow bowlers kept Zimbabwe to 117 for 4 in 30 overs. Read all about the day's action in my match report, which will be up presently. Your commentator today has been Liam Brickhill at Harare Sports Club. Thanks for tuning in, and please do catch our coverage of the next match on Sunday. It's sure to be a cracker! Goodbye

5.15pm Joyous celebration from Zimbabwe's supporters in the ground as Raza and Panyangara embrace in the middle of the pitch. What a match. Ireland fought the hosts for every single run, but Zimbabwe have squeaked home. I need to lie down.

It was said before the match that there is very little indeed to separate these teams, and that's proved to be the case. Their two innings followed remarkably similar courses. Ireland were 39 for 2 in the 10th over, Zimbabwe were 44 for 2 in the 9th. Ireland were 158 for 5 in the 40th over, Zimbabwe were 152 for 5 in the 34th. Ultimately, Raza's frenetic innings at the death proved the difference, and he's named Man of the Match

Vee: "Good to see two evenly matched international sides fight it down to the wire. Close matches like these are what the true international die hard fans want to see. All the way from the West Indies, best of luck to both teams! "
jason gridley: "Raza is a special bloke. Won't be surprised if he ends up leading the side soon. Good role model too "

headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentPreTextItems.html: Raza is eyeing the deep midwicket boundary.

commentTextItems.html: huge cheers erupt as Raza sends the ball down to third man with an angled bat.
hit down the ground, but a diving mid-off cuts it off! That would have been the game, but it's just a single.
wide ball! Murtagh shoots this one down the leg side. Panyangara aimed a Moin Khan-esque flick at it, but couldn't connect. Still, a run and an extra ball for Zimbabwe.
another dot ball, pressure builds. This was on a length outside off. Panyangara wanted the single to third man, but he found point instead.
another dot. It's hard to see where the gap in the field is for Panyangara. He pushes this one to point and charges down the track, but Raza sends him back.

commentPostTextItems.html: In case you're wondering, the light is still good at Harare Sports Club!

commentPreTextItems.html: Zimbabwe need five runs in two overs. There's singing and dancing down at Castle Corner. Porterfield brings the field in with Panyangara on strike.

commentTextItems.html: a length delivery is tapped to mid-on, and there's no run there.

commentPostTextItems.html: george: "a late wicket could make it interesting!"

commentTextItems.html: off the inside edge! Barely a ball has passed without drama in the last 10 minutes. Panyangara stepped forward and wanted to drive down the ground, but the ball flew off the inside edge and went to square leg instead.

commentPostTextItems.html: Six singles in that over. Ireland have to push for the wicket now, and they have Panyangara on strike.

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: clubbed down the ground again. O'Brien sticks out a boot, but he can't stop it and they take a single.
in the air again! This was the leading edge now, and it popped up just past a diving fielder at short extra cover. They charge through for a single, and might have had an overthrow too.

commentPostTextItems.html: 7 off 14 now. Singles will win it for Zimbabwe

commentTextItems.html: smashed back at the bowler! I don't think he got a hand to it, though it was in the air. Just the single

commentPreTextItems.html: Long-off comes up to mid-off now. Third man goes out.

commentTextItems.html: nicely played by the tailender. He gets forward and drives with a straight bat to collect a single to mid-off's right.

commentPreTextItems.html: 11 off 18, two wickets in hand.  A long conference between O'Brien and his captain. Fine leg and third man are up. Long-on and long-off are out.
Dan: "Oh God. I can't read this anymore! Too tense. I'm not even any of these teams' supporters"

commentTextItems.html: short of a good length, Raza slaps it like a tennis forehand down to long-off.

commentPreTextItems.html: The crowd at Castle Corner are all on their feet, and very vocal.

commentTextItems.html: a yorker on middle and off is dug out to mid-off, Panyangara survives.

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: fuller this time, and Panyangara leans forward to drive to point.

commentPreTextItems.html: What's more, Tinashe Panyangara will now be on strike.

commentTextItems.html: a length delivery is met with a dead bat from Panyangara

dismissalText.commentary: Wellington Masakadza run out (Joyce/Porterfield) 10 (18b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 55.55

commentTextItems.html: drama! Is there another twist in this tale? Raza lofted a length delivery out to deep cover, where it fell safely. They took the first two runs easily, but Raza wanted a third. Masakadza committed to the run straight away, but it was never on. Joyce's throw from the deep went to Porterfield at cover, who relayed it to the keeper, catching the batsman well short.
is that another drop? It looked like it! A really tough chance for Wilson behind the stumps. It was another full ball, but this time the shot came off the face of the bat and flew past the keeper.

commentPostTextItems.html: Sanjay: "Almost every Zimbabwe vs Ireland ODIs produced nail bitters.. New Rivalry in cricket?"

commentPreTextItems.html: Raza also brought up Zimbabwe's 200 with the single that brought his fifty.
Trevor: "Come on Castle Corner get the boys home, tune-up Emma, Emmanueri!!"

commentTextItems.html: nicely played by Raza. The ball was full and wide, yorker length really, but he jammed the bat down on it to get the ball through point. Raza always wanted the second run, and returns to his crease as the throw came in.

commentPostTextItems.html: ZCFOutkast: "We can't watch it, but that has to be Raza's finest ODI innings surely - Even though he has 3 tons and one other fifity."

commentTextItems.html: Mooney ends the over with a legitimate bouncer, the left-hander ducking underneath it.

The youngest Masakadza brother, who is left handed, tumbled to his right to hold onto the chance, which was firmly struck. Welcome to international cricket Wellington

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Andy Balbirnie c Masakadza b Jongwe 5 (23b 0x4 0x6 30m) SR: 21.73

dismissalComment.html: another catch for Wellington Masakadza! He seems to have a very safe pair of hands. Balbirnie leaned back to cut, and got a fierce connection on the ball, but couldn't keep the shot down. Masakadza tumbles to his right and holds the ball about a foot off the ground. He's enjoying his debut so far

dismissalText.commentary: Ed Joyce c Chigumbura b Nyumbu 53 (88b 2x4 1x6 110m) SR: 60.22

dismissalComment.html: well, where's this come from? Joyce was looking to open up against Nyumbu, and he cleared his front leg aiming for a slash through the off side. But he hit the ball neither high in the air or along the ground, and picked out Elton Chigumbura to perfection at extra cover. The Zimbabwe captain holds the catch, and an 83 run partnership is broken

dismissalText.commentary: Kevin O'Brien c Waller b Nyumbu 16 (15b 2x4 0x6 12m) SR: 106.66

dismissalComment.html: Waller holds a catch! He would have been under some pressure as this ball rocketed towards him. Kevin O'Brien had jumped down the crease at Nyumbu, who came round the wicket, but the bat turned in his hands as he aimed down the ground. He still got a decent enough connection, but not enough to get the ball past Waller, who set himself under the chance at long off and managed to hold on. That'll be a relief for him.

dismissalText.commentary: Stuart Thompson lbw b Williams 1 (5b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 20

dismissalComment.html: that looks very plumb indeed, and Williams' lbw appeal is quickly upheld. This was quicker and flatter in the air, and it looked as though Thompson couldn't get his bat down quickly enough. Zimbabwe have another, and they're right back into this now

headshotImage.caption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: John Mooney c Jongwe b Masakadza 5 (8b 0x4 0x6 10m) SR: 62.5

dismissalComment.html: a maiden international wicket for Wellington Masakadza! And it took a good catch out in the deep to complete it. Mooney bent low down and then aimed a slog sweep at the Tobacco Stand on the Western side of the ground, but got rather more height than distance. Jongwe was the fielder out there, and he initially ran in before backpedalling a couple of steps and setting himself for the catch. He held on cleanly, and Wellington bent down on one knee midpitch in celebration

headshotImage.caption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Wellington Masakadza player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: George Dockrell st †Mutumbami b Masakadza 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: another for Wellington! Dockrell jumped down the track but swung past a delivery that gripped and turned past his outside edge. There was no mistake from Mutumbami with the gloves, and he's cleanly stumped. Ireland are fading somewhat now after their good start

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamu Chibhabha c Murtagh b McBrine 22 (26b 3x4 0x6 44m) SR: 84.61

dismissalComment.html: he's burgled a wicket! This was much too short again, and Chamu might have put it anywhere on the leg side. But he's picked out Murtagh at short fine leg! The fielder had to bend quite low to hold the catch, but it was straight to him. Chamu had looked untroubled, but he's got to go.

dismissalText.commentary: Richmond Mutumbami c McBrine b Mooney 9 (14b 2x4 0x6 21m) SR: 64.28

dismissalComment.html: gone this time! This one was much fuller from Mooney, and also possibly slower through the air. Mutumbami set himself to whip it through the leg side, but he was much too early on the stroke. Mid-on circles back to hold an easy chance.

dismissalText.commentary: Craig Ervine c †Wilson b McBrine 60 (78b 5x4 0x6 114m) SR: 76.92

dismissalComment.html: what's happened here? Ireland went up in unison as the ball passed Ervine's bat. Wilson also whipped the bails off, but it wasn't the square leg umpire who gave him out. Yep, that's caught behind, and it's a huge dismissal for Ireland.

dismissalText.commentary: Sean Williams st †Wilson b Dockrell 24 (32b 2x4 0x6 41m) SR: 75

dismissalComment.html: stumped! He's got him, and the partnership is broken. Dockrell hasn't been turning the ball, and it's the lack of turn that has done him in. The ball was flighted outside off, and Williams stretched forward to drive. But the ball rushed straight on past him, and Wilson had the bails off in a flash. Ireland have an opening here.

dismissalText.commentary: Elton Chigumbura c †Wilson b Dockrell 16 (22b 1x4 0x6 19m) SR: 72.72

dismissalComment.html: edged, and gone! Well, he edged a couple in the last over, and now one has landed in Wilson's gloves. The ball looked an innocuous one, wide outside off stump, but Chigumbura cut underneath it and Wilson held a sharp chance. Zimbabwe's target is only 96 runs away, but Ireland are keeping themselves in the hunt.

dismissalText.commentary: Sikandar Raza not out 60 (72b 4x4 0x6 107m) SR: 83.33

headshotImage.caption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Malcolm Waller c Thompson b Murtagh 1 (12b 0x4 0x6 15m) SR: 8.33

dismissalComment.html: he's gone! A scratchy innings comes to an end. There was only one fielder left out in the deep, and Waller has picked him out to perfection. Murtagh dug the ball in, and the batsman stepped back to pull in the air ... and Thompson didn't have to move at deep midwicket.

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

headshotImage.caption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Luke Jongwe, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalText.commentary: Luke Jongwe run out (Joyce/McBrine) 5 (9b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, what's happened here? Raza whipped an offspinner off his pads but it went very close to the square leg fielder. Jongwe called for the run, but Raza sent him back. Jongwe was already halfway down the pitch by that stage, and Joyce's throw caught him well short.

headshotImage.longCaption: Tim Murtagh player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Wellington Masakadza run out (Joyce/Porterfield) 10 (18b 0x4 0x6 32m) SR: 55.55

dismissalComment.html: drama! Is there another twist in this tale? Raza lofted a length delivery out to deep cover, where it fell safely. They took the first two runs easily, but Raza wanted a third. Masakadza committed to the run straight away, but it was never on. Joyce's throw from the deep went to Porterfield at cover, who relayed it to the keeper, catching the batsman well short.
